properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 7 at 8:14PM PST until January 8 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibilities in dense fog ranging from 800 feet to as low
as 200 feet.

* WHERE...Fort Tejon area.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Wednesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The California Highway Patrol reported a
visibility of less than one quarter of a mile along Lebec Road.
Low visibilities and hazardous driving conditions are possible
along Interstate 5 through the Grapevine.
properties.instruction:
Anticipate travel delays. If driving, slow down, use low beam
headlights, and leave keep plenty of distance between your vehicle
and the vehicle in front of you.

NWSheadline: A DENSE FOG ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST WEDNESDAY MORNING
